<h2>IV. The Declaration of Independence<br/> as Amended by the<br/> Committee and by Congress</h2>

<div class="docbody">
<p style="text-align: left; text-indent: 0;">[<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Ed. Note:</span> This document is TJs text of the Declaration as copied into his Notes of Proceedings in the Continental Congress, 7 June to 1 Aug. 1776 (which was eventually incorporated in his Autobiography) and is printed above as part of these Notes (q.v., p. 315), above; a facsimile text is available in Boyd, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Declaration of Independence</span>, 1945, pl. <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">viii</span>. This copy (actually there are two, varying in minor particulars; see notes to TJs Notes of Proceedings) carefully records the deletions and insertions made by Congress. The changes made by the Committee of Five and by TJ himself in the second stage of his composition (listed in Boyd, p. 2931) can be discerned by comparing this text with that of the Rough draught and excluding the changes made by Congress.]</p>
</div>
</div><div class="citation_box"><div><span class="bold">Cite as: </span> 
      <span class="italic">The Papers of Thomas Jefferson Digital Edition,</span>
      ed. Barbara B. Oberg and J. Jefferson Looney.
      Charlottesville: University of Virginia Press, Rotunda, 20082015. 
